    {
      "dimension": "api_surface_coherence",
      "identifier": "handler_action_contracts_are_heterogeneous",
      "summary": "Handler dispatch APIs in the same package expose incompatible request/response contracts, especially for action completion and failure signaling.",
      "related_files": [
        "goseg/handler/startram.go",
        "goseg/handler/handler.go",
        "goseg/handler/urbit.go",
        "goseg/handler/urbit_operations.go",
        "goseg/main.go"
      ],
      "evidence": [
        "`StartramHandler` in `goseg/handler/startram.go` wraps each action with `runStartramAsync(...)` and immediately returns `nil`, so caller-visible failures are pushed into internal logs/transitions instead of a unified handler return path.",
        "`UrbitHandler` in `goseg/handler/urbit.go` and other request handlers in `goseg/handler/handler.go` execute and return `error`/payload directly, creating a different API contract for conceptually similar incoming websocket action endpoints.",
        "`main.go` registers multiple handler entrypoints through a shared request path, so this mismatch affects how callers can reliably reason about response/error behavior across action families."
      ],
      "suggestion": "Define one handler contract across action entrypoints in `handler/` (e.g., synchronous result + error, or explicit async operation handle + completion/error channel) and standardize all handler dispatch paths to use it.",
      "confidence": "medium",
      "impact_scope": "subsystem",
      "fix_scope": "multi_file_refactor",
      "root_cause_cluster": "handler_dispatch_contract_drift"
    },
    {
      "dimension": "api_surface_coherence",
      "identifier": "broadcast_to_clients_double_emit",
      "summary": "The broadcast API can emit duplicate auth events and can emit an invalid payload path when JSON marshal fails.",
      "related_files": [
        "goseg/broadcast/broadcast.go"
      ],
      "evidence": [
        "`BroadcastToClients` calls `GetStateJson(bState)` and then `BroadcastAuth(authJson)` before the error check, and calls `BroadcastAuth(authJson)` again when no error occurs.",
        "That means a successful broadcast is emitted twice, and an error path can still trigger a broadcast with potentially nil/undefined bytes before returning."
      ],
      "suggestion": "In `BroadcastToClients`, validate `GetStateJson` error first, return immediately on failure, and emit exactly one auth broadcast on success; optionally dedupe by moving all side effects behind the error check.",
      "confidence": "high",
      "impact_scope": "module",
      "fix_scope": "single_edit"
    },
    {
      "dimension": "api_surface_coherence",
      "identifier": "metric_apis_inconsistent_error_contract",
      "summary": "System telemetry APIs expose inconsistent error signaling for the same conceptual surface (`GetTemp` has no error return while neighboring metrics APIs do).",
      "related_files": [
